// Strings for settings fragment Allow Nox to start alarms Use offset Use wake time
Your bedtime Bedtime offset Length of sleep Wake time
Changes that you make here save automatically Bedtime offset is used if you have bigger time window in which you go to sleep. The offset is applied before the bedtime. Example: If you set your bedtime at 22:00 and offset of 30 minutes, Nox will start monitoring at 21:30. Wake time is used if you want Nox to always wake you up at certain time or before. Example: If you set wake time to 6:00 Nox will start the alarm even if your current sleep time is not yet at the set time
